{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"weekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function, taken together with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_date_time_get_day_of_week()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used to determine the full ISO"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"week date on which "},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is usually equal to the normal Gregorian year (as returned by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_year()"},{"text":"), except as detailed below:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Thursday, the week-numbering year is always equal to the usual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calendar year.  For other days, the number is such that every day","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"within a complete week (Monday to Sunday) is contained within the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"same week-numbering year.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday occurring near the end of the year,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one greater than the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as the Thursday occurring early in the next year)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For Friday, Saturday and Sunday occurring near the start of the year,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one less than the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as the Thursday occurring late in the previous year)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An equivalent description is that the week-numbering year is equal to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the calendar year containing the majority of the days in the current","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"week (Monday to Sunday).","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that January 1 0001 in the proleptic Gregorian calendar is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Monday, so this function never returns 0."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/weeknumberingyear"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/weekNumberingYear","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"weekNumberingYear"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}],"title":"weekNumberingYear","externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE17weekNumberingYearSivp::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib11DateTimeRefV","symbolKind":"property","extendedModule":"GLib","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"text":" falls.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations"]]},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef/weekNumberingYear":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"weekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"title":"weekNumberingYear","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/weeknumberingyear","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/weekNumberingYear","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations":{"type":"topic","title":"DateTimeProtocol Implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","abstract":[],"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/datetimeprotocol-implementations"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DateTimeRef"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef","abstract":[{"code":"GDateTime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into a single structure."}],"title":"DateTimeRef","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DateTimeRef","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"}}}